    Olink Mapping

    olink_mapping.Rmd

    Olink Mapping Dataset

    This dataset provides a mapping of Olink Explore and Target proteins to their corresponding genomic coordinates and gene identifiers. The data is derived from Olink assay data and mapped using BioMart.

    Data Generation Summary

    The mapping was generated using the following steps:

    1. Input Data: Raw data was sourced from Olink Explore and Target assay files (CSV and Excel formats).
    2. Formatting: UniProt IDs and Target Gene symbols were extracted and separated where multiple entries existed.
    3. Mapping: UniProt IDs and HGNC symbols were mapped to Ensembl Gene IDs using biomaRt (Ensembl dataset hsapiens_gene_ensembl).
    4. Filtering:
      • Only protein_coding genes were retained.
      • Only standard chromosomes (1-22, X, Y) were retained.
      • Mappings were filtered to ensure consistency between UniProt gene symbols and Entrez/HGNC/External gene names.
    5. Genomic Positions: Start and End positions were retrieved for both hg19 and hg38 builds using TxDb.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19.knownGene and TxDb.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg38.knownGene.

    Column Descriptions

    Column Description
    UNIPROT UniProt ID provided by Olink
    Target Target gene symbol (HGNC) provided by Olink
    TargetFullName Full protein name provided by Olink
    uniprot_gn_id Mapped UniProt gene ID
    uniprot_gn_symbol Mapped UniProt gene symbol
    entrezgene_id Mapped Entrez gene ID
    entrezgene_accession Mapped Entrez accession
    hgnc_id Mapped HGNC ID
    hgnc_symbol Mapped HGNC symbol
    ensembl_gene_id Mapped Ensembl Gene ID
    external_gene_name External gene name
    gene_biotype Gene biotype (e.g. protein_coding)
    CHR Chromosome name
    START_hg19 Start position (hg19)
    END_hg19 End position (hg19)
    strand_hg19 Strand (hg19)
    START_hg38 Start position (hg38)
    END_hg38 End position (hg38)
    strand_hg38 Strand (hg38)
